{"name":"Escaping Fate","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":"<p>Every time you use an omen there is a 50% chance it is not spent.</p>","rollFormula":"d100","rollLabel":"Escape"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/gutterborn_scum.png","effects":[],"_id":"9rxV1UQ3JIQDYMll"}
{"name":"Gutterborn Scum","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>Small, roll 3d6&minus;2 for Strength. Stealthy, all Presence and Agility tests have their DR reduced by 2 (normal tests are DR10 instead of DR12). Roll d6 on the weapon table and d2 on the armor table. You also begin with one specialty:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Coward's Jab</li>\n<li>Filthy Fingersmith</li>\n<li>Abominable Gob Lobber</li>\n<li>Escaping Fate</li>\n<li>Excretal Stealth</li>\n<li>Dodging Death</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The first time the Scum gets better another specialty is rolled. From the second time the Scum gets better it&rsquo;s possible to reroll these two specialities or just one.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","armorTableDie":"1d2","description":"An ill star smiled upon your birth. Poverty, crime and bad parenting didn’t help either. In your community an honest day’s work was never an option. Not that you ever tried, what are you, some kind of mug? A razor blade and a moonless night are worth a week of chump-work.","omenDie":"1d2","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d6","startingItems":"","startingPresence":"3d6","startingRolls":"morkborg.rolls-gutterborn-scum,Specialities,1\nmorkborg.rolls-gutterborn-scum,Bad Birth,1","startingSilver":"1d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6-2","startingToughness":"3d6","weaponTableDie":"1d6"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/gutterborn_scum.png","effects":[],"_id":"G3dMTAupnnM3fyJv"}
{"name":"Filthy Fingersmith","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":"<p>Your snaky little digits get into pockets and pick locks with a DR8 Agility test. You also begin with lockpicks!</p>","rollFormula":"1d20+@abilities.agility.value","rollLabel":"Pick"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/gutterborn_scum.png","effects":[],"_id":"XZSwJEeyrYzm7X0q"}
{"name":"Coward's Jab","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":"<p>When attacking by surprise test Agility DR10. On a success you automatically hit once with a light one-handed weapon, dealing normal damage +3.</p>","rollFormula":"1d20+@abilities.agility.value","rollLabel":"Jab"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/gutterborn_scum.png","effects":[],"_id":"aOwKOQge7XSi5Mma"}
{"name":"Abominable Gob Lobber","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":"<p>Your phlegm is viscous, lumpy, vile and ballistically accurate at short range. You can spit d2 times during a fight. Roll a DR8 Presence test for accuracy. Targets are blinded, retching and vomiting for d4 rounds. Anyone witnessing this&mdash;friend and foe&mdash;must make a Toughness test to not also vomit. PCs test DR10 and enemies DR12.</p>","rollFormula":"1d20+@abilities.presence.value","rollLabel":"Spit"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/gutterborn_scum.png","effects":[],"_id":"axezfdMiSmBjGkBD"}
{"name":"Excretal Stealth","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":"<p>You have an astounding, almost preternatural ability to hide in muck, debris and filth. When hidden in these conditions a DR16 Presence test is required to notice you.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/gutterborn_scum.png","effects":[],"_id":"gMnRFwEfMR2pzf63"}
{"name":"Dodging Death","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":"<p>You are so unpleasant, irrelevant, disgusting and vile even Death would rather avoid you if it can. On death, if there is even the slightest possibility that you survived, there is a 50% chance that you did. If successful, after 10 rounds you pop back up with d4 HP and an unlikely explanation of your escape.</p>","rollFormula":"1d100","rollLabel":"Dodge"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/tokens/players/gutterborn_scum.png","effects":[],"_id":"rYKa7uAqLp6KyZsP"}
